content.description:
Grab a set of side pulls with good low feet. Pull up onto the boulder and work up on small, but positive crimps to a to large holds and a mantle over the top.

50yds west of the north end of the lighthouse. From the path leading right from the lightouse take the 3rd trail on the left through the vegetation. The trail leads directly to the base of the route.
Flat pebble/sand landing. Pad is helpful, but not necessary.

Ship's Prow is bulging prow of rock forming an overhang ten feet above the base, with two horizontal cracks leading to the bulge. Climb up to the lower horizontal, then pull into the 2nd horizontal to set up for the reach to the positive holds and pull over the top. While the horizontals and the holds on Ship's Prow are secure and positive the blocky landing and suspect blocks above the bulge make a fall serious at best.

20 yds west of the north end of the lighthouse.
Spotter/Multiple Pads
The rocky beach at the Amphitrite Lighhouse offers a variety of water and surf weathered Basalt boulders. While not a destination the rocky beach provides some entertaining problems.
